<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>If you&#39;re interested in using Hugo for a static blog, and want to post from Org-mode I&#39;ve just uploaded <a href="https://weblog.masukomi.org/2024/07/19/using-org-mode-with-hugo/">a blog post</a> you&#39;ll probably find useful.</p> <p>For folks who are already using ox-hugo, it includes code for creating two new org links so that you can insert <code>ref</code> and <code>relref</code> shortcode links using the standard <code>C-c C-l</code> and navigating to the file so that you don&#39;t make typos.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/masukomi"> /u/masukomi </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/1e7ach0/tips_advice_on_using_oxhugo_to_blog_with_orgmode/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/1e7ach0/tips_advice_on_using_oxhugo_to_blog_with_orgmode/">[comments]</a></span>